The fs module 
provides an API 
for interacting with the file system 
in a manner closely modeled around standard POSIX (The Portable Operating System Interface) functions.

To use this module:
const fs = require('fs');

fs.appendFile(path, data[, options], callback)
// path <string> | <Buffer> | <URL> | <number> filename or file descriptor
// data <string> | <Buffer>









